Net Profit (TTM/latest) (2025-10-14): 1.48M

Title   : Hilton signs new 195 room hotel in Chennai with MGM Group 
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-10-14T11:19:07
Fetched : 2025-10-14T15:05:26.870822
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/hilton-signs-new-195-room-hotel-in-chennai-with-mgm-group/article70162054.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Hospitality major Hilton has expanded its presence in Chennai with the signing of Hilton Chennai Egmore.
The new 195-room hotel will be developed in partnership with MKR Estate Developers, part of the MGM Healthcare Group.
The hotel, expected to open in January 2029, will be part of a larger mixed-use development that also includes a commercial office complex, the company said in a release. The new hotel will expand the presence of Hilton’s flagship brand, Hilton Hotels & Resorts, in the city, joining Hilton Chennai.
With nearly 17,000 sq. ft. of event space, including two ballrooms, a meeting room and a boardroom, Hilton Chennai Egmore will serve as a premium venue for corporate gatherings, conferences, and social celebrations in the city, the company added in the release.
Hilton had earlier announced plans to double its brand footprint over the next five years. As part of this strategy, they have announced the debut of their first LXR Hotels and Resorts property in India, slated to open in Bengaluru in 2026.
Published on October 14, 2025

Title   : Hilton inks 195-key Hilton Chennai Egmore in partnership with MKR Estate Developers
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-10-14T10:42:44
Fetched : 2025-10-14T15:05:26.870854
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/hilton-inks-195-key-hilton-chennai-egmore-in-partnership-with-mkr-estate-developers/article70162072.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Hilton on Tuesday announced the signing of 195-key Hilton Chennai Egmore in partnership with MKR Estate Developers, part of the MGM Healthcare Group.
The hotel is expected to open in January 2029. It will be part of a larger mixed-use development that also includes a commercial office complex, Hilton said in a statement.
"The signing of Hilton Chennai Egmore is a significant step in strengthening our South India portfolio. Chennai is an anchor market for both business and leisure travellers, and this new property allows us to serve the city's growing demand for elevated hospitality experiences at corporate and social events," Zubin Saxena, senior vice president and country head, Hilton, South Asia, said.
Radisson Hotel Group on Tuesday announced the opening of 80-key Park Inn by Radisson Lucknow Vikas Nagar and 108-key Radisson Hotel Prayagraj in Uttar Pradesh.
"The opening of two hotels in Lucknow and Prayagraj marks a significant step in our expansion journey across North India.
"As we continue to strengthen our footprint in high-potential state capitals and tier II cities, our focus remains on creating meaningful value for guests and partners while contributing to the region's economic and tourism growth," Radisson Hotel Group Managing Director and COO, South Asia, Nikhil Sharma said in a statement.
Published on October 14, 2025

