Published: 2025-10-14T14:53:43
Fetched : 2025-10-14T16:31:43.314695
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/money-and-banking/zaggle-ropes-in-ayush-mhatre-as-brand-ambassador/article70163227.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Zaggle ropes in Ayush Mhatre as brand ambassador Ayush, who represents the country’s U19 team, plays for Mumbai in domestic cricket and the Chennai Super Kings in the Indian Premier League (IPL) By BL Hyderabad Bureau Updated - October 14, 2025  at 08:23 PM. | Hyderabad × Share WhatsApp X Facebook LinkedIn Messenger Reddit Mail https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/money-and-banking/zaggle-ropes-in-ayush-mhatre-as-brand-ambassador/article70163227.ece Copy Cricketer Ayush Mhatre, the new Zaggle brand ambassador Zaggle , a spend management solutions company has roped in cricketer Ayush Mhatre as its brand ambassador. Ayush, who represents the country’s U19 team, plays for Mumbai in domestic cricket and the Chennai Super Kings in the Indian Premier League (IPL). “This five-year partnership will help us increase our engagement with the country’s digitally savvy consumers and businesses,” Raj P Narayanam, Founder and Executive Chairman of Zaggle, said in a statement on Tuesday. The company signed ace bowler Jasprit Bumrah in 2017 and all-rounder Hardik Pandya in 2018. Comments Published on  October 14, 2025 READ MORE THIS AD SUPPORTS OUR JOURNALISM. SUBSCRIBE FOR MINIMAL ADS. THIS AD SUPPORTS OUR JOURNALISM. SUBSCRIBE FOR MINIMAL ADS. THIS AD SUPPORTS OUR JOURNALISM. SUBSCRIBE FOR MINIMAL ADS.

Title   : Broker’s call: Zaggle (Buy) 
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-10-14T11:53:52
Fetched : 2025-10-14T16:31:43.314736
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/brokers-call-zaggle-buy/article70162597.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Target: ₹520
CMP: ₹344.75
Zaggle Prepaid Ocean Services (Zaggle) is a home-grown SaaS-fintech platform that helps businesses digitise spending across employee reimbursements, vendor payments, channel partner rewards and incentives, along with a host of expanding use cases.
Founded in 2011, the company has steadily evolved from a corporate gifting player into a full-scale enterprise spend management platform. Its key products such as Save, Propel and Zoyer allow corporates to automate and track spends, while newer product launches are adding analytics and international payment capabilities.
With a robust customer acquisition model, Zaggle has built strong partnerships with 19 banks and all major card networks. The company has issued 50mn+ prepaid cards for over 3,550 corporates with around 3.3mn active users, while operating an asset-light model with high customer stickiness.
Monetisation includes SaaS subscription fees, interchange income and merchant commissions. With rising cross-sell via ecosystem play, growing adoption of digital spend tools and a strong portfolio of enterprise clients, Zaggle is perfectly positioned to benefit from the sustained formalisation of business spends in India.
We initiate coverage on Zaggle with a Buy rating and a Sep’26 TP of ₹520, valuing the company at 30x Sep’27E EPS, slightly conservative compared to other B2B internet peers considering the recent margin dip and the rise in working capital requirement for Propel.
Published on October 14, 2025

